These scallion pancake “hot pockets” combines some of my favorite childhood classics into one. It’s truly the perfect savory snack–crispy scallion pancake stuffed with spam, egg, and cheese. 

We used @laobandumplings’ new scallion pancakes as the vehicle for this creation, holding all the delicious filling together before being pan-fried to golden, crispy perfection. Each bite delivers a satisfying flaky crust with a rich, melty center that perfectly captures nostalgic comfort wrapped up in a handheld treat.

Find @laobandumplings’ new Crunchy Bites products, Scallion Pancakes and Crab Rangoon at @wholefoods!

Ingredients:
2 frozen @laobandumplings scallion pancakes
1/3 can spam, diced
2 eggs
Handful of shredded mozzarella cheese
1 stalk scallion, thinly sliced
Neutral oil, as needed
Salt and white pepper as needed
Sesame seeds, optional

Dipping sauce:
2 tbsp mayo
1 tsp hot sauce
1 tsp lemon juice

Method:
Remove frozen scallion pancake from packaging and let it thaw on lightly floured countertop while you prepare the other ingredients.
Dice spam into small cubes. Add neutral oil in a pan and fry until golden brown. Set aside.
Beat together 2 eggs with scallions, salt, and white pepper.
Add more oil into pan and pour in eggs. Cook until desired doneness and remove from pan. Set aside.
Place spam, eggs, and cheese onto the thawed scallion pancake.
Fold in half and seal edges with a fork.
Sprinkle sesame seeds on both sides.
Add oil to a pan and pan fry on medium heat until both sides are crispy. 
Remove from pan and let it cool for a few minutes. 
Enjoy on its own or with a dipping sauce.
